{
  "stem": "13079.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Court was appointed by General Lucian Truscott.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was known as a military government court and was composed of approximately nine members, one of whom was the president of court.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that position was held in all the cases usually by a general officer, that is, either a major general or brigadier general.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The prosecution staff was also appointed by General Truscott with the aid of the war crimes branch of [?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Yuspet ?] and of headquarters Third Army.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that same thing was true in respect to all four cases.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "When I say four cases, I mean Dachau, Mauthausen, Flossenburg, and Buchenwald.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the personnel of the courts were usually nine field grade officers.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That meant that they were at the rank of major and above.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And most of them were full colonels, men who had served approximately 25 to 30 years in the army and were men of experience.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And their function here in this trial as members of the court were to act as fact [? miners, ?] like a jury would act.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But it was more than that because they also participated in the determination of what sentence each one of their accused was to receive.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And the defense counsel were those that were not only appointed by the court but also those that were selected by their accused.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "In other words, each accused in-- in every one of these trials had the right to be represented by a lawyer of his choice.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And Uncle Sam footed the bill for the [INAUDIBLE] fees.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And a lot of the accused were content to have those officers and men, who had been appointed as defense counsel, by the appointing authority to serve him in their defense.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
